These wines and spirits proudly bear the name of St. Edmund Hall, one of the 32 independent institutions of learning which, collectively, comprise the University of Oxford. St. Edmund Hall, which can be identified on the ancient map above (1713), dates its origin back to the 13th Century. Some of you may have seen St. Edmund Hall’s medieval library which ap- peared so prominently in the recent film “Accident.” It is with no small sense of pride that we offer these carefully selected wines and spirits to the discriminating drinkers of New York.
